    &lt;CommentText&gt;I have been trying to contact the PALS team since Monday ref. an existing complaint they are making official and I want to make some amendments. The PALS team never answer the phone so you are constantly leaving messages which you are told you will get a call back. I asked to speak to someone senior on Tuesday as I hadn't got anywhere and spoke to the senior nurse on call and they said they would get someone to call me on Thursday as I explained I was on a course Wednesday.  I received a call Tuesday evening but as I was on a course (thought as closed I wasn't expecting them to call) so I had to apologise for my phone going off. Then on Wednesday I got 3 more calls and I had to phone them in a break to say please stop calling me as I am on a course and asked not to be called. I was told I would get a call Thursday. I've tried to call them numerous times today but again no answer and leave a message but people must have the same problem as the mail box is now full. I phoned the switchboard to ask to speak to someone and they put me through to whoever is in charge of the hospital I presume some sort of CEO/Chief and they were so unhelpful and they just said I will get someone to call you but I can't say when - I've had numerous people tell me the same thing - What do you have to do to talk to someone???????&lt;/CommentText&gt;
